  "text": "In this section, we evaluate the performance of the proposed model and compare it with the state-of-the-art solution [CITATION_1] . In that work [CITATION_2] , a position-aware HAR was proposed based on a three level classifier: the first-level classifier was used to distinguish between dynamic and static activities, the second-level classifier was used to detect the position of the sensor, and the third-level had a set of activity recognition classifiers each belonging to specific position. This method uses handcrafted features and Random Forest classifier [CITATION_3] .",
